&lt;p&gt;BIRMINGHAM COMMUNITY HEALTHCARE NHS FOUNDATION TRUST&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Children’s Community Speech and Language Therapy Service&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Children and Families Division&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Location: BCHC Plus SaLT Service - Citywide&lt;br /&gt;Grade: Band 5 Post&lt;br /&gt;Hours: TTO - Full-Time/Part-time&lt;br /&gt;Contract type: Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to the continued growth of our BCHC Plus Speech and Language Therapy Team, we are recruiting to a permanent Band 5 position. The role is Term Time Only. We welcome applications from experienced Band 5 therapists and from newly qualified practitioners. Support will be provided for successful candidates who are working towards RCSLT competencies.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are recruiting individuals with a passion for developing their career as an SLT within school and nursery environments. Applicants must have established clinical and negotiation skills, and recent experience of working within schools, either on placement or as a qualified therapist. Applicants must be able to work with a range of client groups and travel to sites across the city of Birmingham.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The BCHC Plus SLT Service is an enthusiastic team consisting of Band 5 and Band 6 SLTs, dedicated admin support, and a Team Leader. The team has established a reputation for service excellence and enviable customer feedback. SLTs are encouraged to contribute to service development, and we value new ideas and experiences.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We deliver clinical excellence through Universal, Targeted and Specialist approaches tailored to the schools’ and children’s individual needs, to provide an efficient and effective service. Working in this way provides ample opportunities to develop a broad range of clinical skills with a variety of client groups.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our well-established working relationships with other agencies have enabled us to play an active part in the development of the Citywide strategy for children with SLCN.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The BCHC Plus SLT Service forms part of a large and forward-thinking Children’s Speech and Language Therapy Service, part of the Children and Families Division of BCHC NHS Trust. We are able to offer a supportive working environment with access to specialist clinical support and an emphasis on sharing good practice through effective team working and encourage continuing professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please contact Laura Adlington (Team Leader) if you would like to discuss the role.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameLaura AdlingtonJob titleTeam LeaderEmail addresslaura.adlington@bhamcommunity.nhs.ukTelephone number07701 293 974&lt;/p&gt;
